- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is likely because the paper discusses a recommendation system for push notifications/pop-ups, which involves analyzing user behavior and preferences to improve the delivery and retention rates of advertisements. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely because the paper uses deep neural networks (DNNs) to develop the recommendation system. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possibility because the paper aims to decrease the troublesome to users while increasing the click-through rate of push notifications/pop-ups, which involves understanding user behavior and preferences. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a potential category because the paper deals with connecting and maintaining relationships with app users through push notifications/pop-ups. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible because the paper involves analyzing user behavior and preferences, which could involve natural language processing techniques.
